[{"id":"VH897175","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Consider the series <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the sum, from n equals 1, to infinity of, open parenthesis, negative 1, close parenthesis, raised to the n plus 1 power, times a, sub n\"><math alttext=\"the sum, from n equals 1, to infinity of, open parenthesis, negative 1, close parenthesis, raised to the n plus 1 power, times a, sub n\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><munderover><mo>∑</mo><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>∞</mi></mrow></munderover><mrow><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow></mstyle></mrow></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a, sub n, is greater than the fraction 1 over n\"><math alttext=\"a, sub n, is greater than the fraction 1 over n\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> for all <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n\"><math alttext=\"n\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and the sequence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open curly bracket, a, sub n, close curly bracket\"><math alttext=\"open curly bracket, a, sub n, close curly bracket\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>{</mo><msub><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo>}</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> decreases with limit 0. Which of the following statements is true?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH897175_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The series converges absolutely.</p>",